class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> topKFrequent(vector<int>& nums, int k) 
    {
        vector<int> res;
        unordered_map<int,int> freq;
        for(auto& ele:nums)
        {
            freq[ele]++;
        }

        priority_queue< pair<int,int>,
                        vector<pair<int,int>>,
                        greater<pair<int,int>> > minheap;
        
        for(auto& ele:freq)
        {
            minheap.push({ele.second,ele.first});
            if(minheap.size()>k) minheap.pop();
        }

        while(!minheap.empty())
        {
            res.push_back(minheap.top().second);
            minheap.pop();
        }
        return res;
    }
};

Time Complexity: O(n + m log k)

- Building the frequency map takes O(n).
- Let m be the number of unique elements.
- Each unique element is inserted into the min-heap of size at most k.
- Each push/pop operation takes O(log k).
- Therefore, total time = O(n + m log k).

(In the worst case, m = n, so the complexity becomes O(n log k).)

Space Complexity: O(m + k)

- Frequency map stores m unique elements → O(m).
- Min-heap stores at most k elements → O(k).
- Result array stores k elements.
